HEADWORD: Electrine
<hw>E*lec"trine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>electrinus</ets> of amber. See <er>Electric</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Belonging to, or made of, amber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Made of electrum, an alloy used by the
ancients.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electrition</ent>⟦br⟧
